          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "In part 1 the targets were prepared from the chemical",
                "compound 238UF(4) using natural uranium. Layers of",
                "488, 408 and 451 ug/cm2 238UF(4) were evaporated on",
                "backing foils of 42 ug/cm2 carbon and subsequently",
                "covered with carbon layers of 10, in a few cases also",
                "of 20 ug/cm2. In parts 2 and 3 metallic uranium targets",
                "were used. Metallic 238U electrodes with a 235U",
                "depletion to 0.2% were the starting material. The",
                "thickness of the uranium layers was about 300 ug/cm2.",
                "In all parts of the experiment a carbon foil of",
                "30 ug/cm2 thickness was placed at a distance of 125 mm",
                "behind the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The evaporated residues (ERs) were separated",
                "from the beam by the velocity filter SHIP and",
                "implanted into a position-sensitive strip Si detector",
                " (focal-plane stop detector)"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The detector system was completed by a Si veto detector",
                "and a Ge clover detector, both mounted behind the",
                "stop detector. The clover detector was separated from",
                "the SHIP vacuum by a 1 mm thick aluminium window. The",
                "detector consisted of four Ge crystals, each with a",
                "diameter of 50 mm and a length of 70 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
